<p><i><b>From the Hip</b></i>, is a 1987 <a href="/wiki/Courtroom_drama" title="Courtroom drama" class="mw-redirect">courtroom</a> dramedy film directed by <a href="/wiki/Bob_Clark" title="Bob Clark">Bob Clark</a> from a screenplay by Bob Clark and <a href="/wiki/David_E._Kelley" title="David E. Kelley">David E. Kelley</a>. The film stars <a href="/wiki/Judd_Nelson" title="Judd Nelson">Judd Nelson</a>, <a href="/wiki/Elizabeth_Perkins" title="Elizabeth Perkins">Elizabeth Perkins</a>, <a href="/wiki/John_Hurt" title="John Hurt">John Hurt</a> and <a href="/wiki/Beatrice_Winde" title="Beatrice Winde">Beatrice Winde</a>.</p>
<p></p>
